details.name: Percey
details.description: A trim update on an old stalwart, Percey is a bookish, modern classic.

details.name: Anders
details.description: With a generously rounded browline and flattering medium fit, Anders is a surefire crowd-pleaser.

details.name: Watts
details.description: An oversized, round eyeframe lends Watts a charmingly learned look. Slim temple arms and a keyhole bridge add a dose of midcentury panache. Perfect for bookworms and cool cats alike.

details.name: Everson
details.description: Everson is a wide-fit, rectangular frame with a twist: a subtle, angular dip in its browline that invites double takes.

details.name: Moriarty
details.description: Moriarty's charm is in the details: screws that stud the acetate lens rims, subtle divots on either side of the bridge, and polished metal along the temple arms and browline. (Plus adjustable nose pads for an effortless fit.)

details.name: York
details.description: York, a vintage-style aviator frame from our Luminary Collection, features a classic teardrop shape and premium Japanese titanium construction.

details.name: Lyle
details.description: A keyhole bridge and classic round frames make Lyle a frame for day and evening alike.

details.name: Bowen
details.description: Bowen's chiseled corners, straight browline, and wide fit make it an understated but unmistakably dashing frame.

details.name: Abbott
details.description: Abbott is unapologetically round and effortlessly iconic—it’s also constructed from premium Japanese titanium.
